<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="5" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[826,1429,1709,1844]" pageId="3" pageNumber="5">
Diagnosis — Female with sternal setae st2, st3, and st4 on an undivided shield (
<bibRefCitation author="Karg W." box="[1235,1372,1744,1768]" pageId="3" pageNumber="5" pagination="51 - 61" refId="ref10075" refString="Karg W. 1997 a - Neue Raubmilbenarten der Antennophoridae Berlese, 1892 (Acarina, Parasitiformes), phoretisch auf Passaliden - Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischem Museum in Berlin, 73 (1): 51 - 61." type="journal article" year="1997">Karg 1997a</bibRefCitation>
and present publication, 
<figureCitation box="[1066,1165,1779,1803]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="10.[281,293,1883,1902]" captionTargetBox="[284,1299,356,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-5@10.[281,1306,340,1852]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6:: Holostethus longosetis n. sp. Female. a – Venter; b – Pedipalpus, 245 µm; c – Chelicera, 88 µm long." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5404306" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5404306/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="5">Figure 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[826,1429,1709,1844]" box="[864,1198,1820,1844]" pageId="3" pageNumber="5">We distinguish two families:</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[863,1219,1873,1897]" box="[863,1219,1873,1897]" pageId="3" pageNumber="5">
• 
<taxonomicName authority="Tragardh, 1937" authorityName="Tragardh" authorityYear="1937" box="[892,1219,1873,1897]" class="Arachnida" family="Fedrizziidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Fedrizziidae Trägårdh, 1937</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[863,1320,1924,1948]" box="[863,1320,1924,1948]" pageId="3" pageNumber="5">• Klinkowstroemiidae Trägårdh, 1946.</paragraph>
<paragraph box="[210,232,250,269]" pageId="4" pageNumber="6">W</paragraph>
<paragraph box="[232,236,250,269]" pageId="4" pageNumber="6">.</paragraph>
<paragraph box="[240,276,250,269]" pageId="4" pageNumber="6">and</paragraph>
<paragraph box="[281,406,250,269]" pageId="4" pageNumber="6">Schorlemmer</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[666,910,327,372]" box="[666,910,327,372]" pageId="4" pageNumber="6">Trigynaspida</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5404298" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5404298" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5404298/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="6" startId="4.[159,171,1302,1321]" targetBox="[203,1374,420,1247]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[159,1429,1302,1655]" pageId="4" pageNumber="6">
FIGURE 2: Cladogram of the subgroups of Trigynaspida 
<bibRefCitation author="Camin J. H. &amp; Gorirossi F." box="[693,927,1302,1321]" pageId="4" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 70" refId="ref9017" refString="Camin J. H., Gorirossi F. 1955 - A revision of the suborder Mesostigmata, Acarina, based on new interpretations of comparative morphological data - The Chicago Academy of Sciences Special Publication 11: 1 - 70." type="journal article" year="1955">Camin et Gorirossi, 1955</bibRefCitation>
, synapomorphies (1 – 4) and autapomorphies (5 – 9), characteristics for the Super-families of Trigynaspida; our present results confirm previous findings:
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[159,1429,1302,1655]" box="[193,1004,1357,1377]" pageId="4" pageNumber="6">
1 – Sternal shield divided into 2 to 3 parts, as an exception undivided (
<figureCitation box="[853,940,1357,1377]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="7.[305,317,1883,1902]" captionTargetBox="[255,1346,350,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-4@7.[234,1354,340,1852]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4: Pyrosejus verticis n. sp. Female. a – Venter; b – Tectum, 34 µm wide; c – Chelicera, 35 µm long." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5404302" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5404302/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="6">Figures 4</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[986,997,1357,1376]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="10.[281,293,1883,1902]" captionTargetBox="[284,1299,356,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-5@10.[281,1306,340,1852]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6:: Holostethus longosetis n. sp. Female. a – Venter; b – Pedipalpus, 245 µm; c – Chelicera, 88 µm long." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5404306" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5404306/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="6">6</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[159,1429,1302,1655]" box="[193,941,1385,1405]" pageId="4" pageNumber="6">
2 – Sternal shield as a rule divided into 2 to 6 parts (
<figureCitation box="[678,757,1385,1404]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="7.[305,317,1883,1902]" captionTargetBox="[255,1346,350,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-4@7.[234,1354,340,1852]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4: Pyrosejus verticis n. sp. Female. a – Venter; b – Tectum, 34 µm wide; c – Chelicera, 35 µm long." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5404302" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5404302/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="6">Figure 4</figureCitation>
), Baker 
<emphasis box="[833,875,1385,1404]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="6">et al.</emphasis>
, (1958)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[159,1429,1302,1655]" box="[193,1084,1413,1432]" pageId="4" pageNumber="6">
3 – Latigynial shields well developed, as a rule separate jugular shields (
<figureCitation box="[870,949,1413,1432]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="7.[305,317,1883,1902]" captionTargetBox="[255,1346,350,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-4@7.[234,1354,340,1852]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4: Pyrosejus verticis n. sp. Female. a – Venter; b – Tectum, 34 µm wide; c – Chelicera, 35 µm long." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5404302" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5404302/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="6">Figure 4</figureCitation>
), 
<bibRefCitation author="Karg W." box="[966,1084,1413,1432]" pageId="4" pageNumber="6" pagination="51 - 61" refId="ref10075" refString="Karg W. 1997 a - Neue Raubmilbenarten der Antennophoridae Berlese, 1892 (Acarina, Parasitiformes), phoretisch auf Passaliden - Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischem Museum in Berlin, 73 (1): 51 - 61." type="journal article" year="1997">Karg (1997a)</bibRefCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[159,1429,1302,1655]" box="[193,1299,1441,1460]" pageId="4" pageNumber="6">4 – Three primary shields protecting the genital orifice of females, tarsus IV of adults and deuto-nymphs with 21 setae</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[159,1429,1302,1655]" pageId="4" pageNumber="6">
(formula: 4, 3/3, 1/1, 3/3, 3), deuto-nymphs with podonotal, mesonotal and pygidial shields (
<bibRefCitation author="Krantz G. W. &amp; Ainscough B. D." box="[1092,1339,1468,1488]" pageId="4" pageNumber="6" pagination="583 - 665" refId="ref10622" refString="Krantz G. W., Ainscough B. D. 1990 - Acarina: Mesostigmata (Gamasida) - Soil Biology Guide. Edited by Daniel L. Dindal: 583 - 665." type="book chapter" year="1990">Krantz &amp; Ainscough 1990</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans G. O. &amp; Till W. M." pageId="4" pageNumber="6" pagination="139 - 270" refId="ref9301" refString="Evans G. O., Till W. M. 1979 - Mesostigmatic mites of Britain and Ireland (Chelicerata: Acari- Parasitiformes), an introduction to their external morphology and classification - Transactions of The Zoological Society of London, 35: 139 - 270." type="journal article" year="1979">Evans &amp; Till 1979</bibRefCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[159,1429,1302,1655]" box="[193,1225,1524,1543]" pageId="4" pageNumber="6">
5 – Male aperture at the anterior margin of sternum (
<bibRefCitation author="Hirschmann W. &amp; Zirngiebl-Nicol I." box="[687,1027,1524,1543]" pageId="4" pageNumber="6" refId="ref9456" refString="Hirschmann W., Zirngiebl-Nicol I. 1961 - Die Gattung Trichouropoda Berlese, 1916, die Cheliceren und das System der Uropodiden - Acarologie, Schriftenreihe fur Vergleichende Milbenkunde, 4. Folge, Teil 4, pp. 41." type="journal volume" year="1961">Hirschmann &amp; Zirngiebl-Nicol 1961</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans G. O. &amp; Till W. M." box="[1036,1219,1524,1543]" pageId="4" pageNumber="6" pagination="139 - 270" refId="ref9301" refString="Evans G. O., Till W. M. 1979 - Mesostigmatic mites of Britain and Ireland (Chelicerata: Acari- Parasitiformes), an introduction to their external morphology and classification - Transactions of The Zoological Society of London, 35: 139 - 270." type="journal article" year="1979">Evans and Till 1979</bibRefCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[159,1429,1302,1655]" box="[193,690,1552,1571]" pageId="4" pageNumber="6">
6 – Adults with two shields on the dorsum (
<figureCitation box="[605,683,1552,1571]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="6.[464,476,1883,1902]" captionTargetBox="[264,1336,358,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-5@6.[249,1338,340,1852]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3: Pyrosejus verticis n. sp. Female. Dorsum, 348 – 374 µm long." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5404300" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5404300/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="6">Figure 3</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[159,1429,1302,1655]" box="[193,1053,1580,1599]" pageId="4" pageNumber="6">
7 – Female with sternal setae st2, st3 and st4 on an undivided shield (
<figureCitation box="[840,919,1580,1599]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="10.[281,293,1883,1902]" captionTargetBox="[284,1299,356,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-5@10.[281,1306,340,1852]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6:: Holostethus longosetis n. sp. Female. a – Venter; b – Pedipalpus, 245 µm; c – Chelicera, 88 µm long." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5404306" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5404306/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="6">Figure 6</figureCitation>
), 
<bibRefCitation author="Karg W." box="[935,1053,1580,1599]" pageId="4" pageNumber="6" pagination="51 - 61" refId="ref10075" refString="Karg W. 1997 a - Neue Raubmilbenarten der Antennophoridae Berlese, 1892 (Acarina, Parasitiformes), phoretisch auf Passaliden - Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischem Museum in Berlin, 73 (1): 51 - 61." type="journal article" year="1997">Karg (1997a)</bibRefCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[159,1429,1302,1655]" box="[193,1115,1607,1627]" pageId="4" pageNumber="6">
8 – In adults latigynial shields and mesogynial shields coalesced (
<bibRefCitation author="Hunter P. E. &amp; Costa, M." box="[807,1006,1607,1626]" pageId="4" pageNumber="6" pagination="233 - 240" refId="ref9498" refString="Hunter P. E., Costa, M. 1970 - Two new African Species of Megisthanus Thorell Mesostigmata: Megisthanidae - Florida Entomologist 53 (4): 233 - 240. doi: 10.2307 / 3493194" type="journal article" year="1970">
Hunter &amp; 
<collectingRegion box="[903,956,1607,1626]" country="New Zealand" name="West Coast" pageId="4" pageNumber="6">Costa</collectingRegion>
1970
</bibRefCitation>
, Karg 1997)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[159,1429,1302,1655]" box="[193,844,1635,1655]" pageId="4" pageNumber="6">
9 – Sternal shield of adults divided into 4 to 6 parts (
<bibRefCitation author="Baker E. W. &amp; Camin J. H. &amp; Cunliffe F. &amp; Woolley T. &amp; Yunker C. E." box="[682,838,1635,1655]" pageId="4" pageNumber="6" pagination="44 - 48" refId="ref8866" refString="Baker E. W., Camin J. H., Cunliffe F., Woolley T. A, Yunker C. E., 1958 - Guide to the families of Mites - Contribution number 3 of The Institute of Acarology, Department of Zoology, University of Maryland, College Park, pp. 230. Berker J. 1956 - 1. Uber die Bedeutung der Raubmilben innerhalb der Spinnmilbenbiozonose auf Apfel 2. uber den Einfluss zweier Raubmilben auf den Populationsverlauf von Metatetranychus ulmi Koch - Mitteilungen der Biologischen. Bundesanstalt fur Land- u. Forstwirtschaft, Berlin-Dahlem 85: 44 - 48." type="journal article" year="1958">
Baker 
<emphasis box="[742,785,1635,1654]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="6">et al.</emphasis>
, 1958
</bibRefCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[159,762,1719,1849]" pageId="4" pageNumber="6">
One new species belongs to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tragardh" authorityYear="1937" box="[609,758,1719,1743]" class="Arachnida" family="Fedrizziidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="4" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Fedrizziidae</taxonomicName>
. This species differs decisively from the hitherto known species. It proved to be necessary to erect a new genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
